HEADWORD: Disposed
<hw>Dis*posed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Inclined; minded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When he was <qex>disposed</qex> to pass into Achaia.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts xviii. 27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inclined to mirth; jolly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Well disposed</b></col>, <cd>in good condition; in good
health.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disposedness</ent>⟦br⟧
